### Test Refresh Token Endpoint
### Before using this file, you need to login first to get a valid refresh token

### 1. Register a user (if needed)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
X-Recaptcha-Token: test-token

{
  "email": "test.refresh@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!",
  "terms_accepted": true,
  "kvkk_consent_accepted": true
}

###

### 2. Login to get tokens
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test.refresh@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

###

### 3. Test refresh token endpoint with valid refresh token
# Copy the refresh_token from login response and paste below
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

###

### 4. Test with invalid refresh token
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "invalid.token.here"
}

###

### 5. Test with missing refresh token
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{}